Governor Mai Mala Buni of Yobe state has visited Buni Gari and Buni Yadi in Gujba local government area of Yobe state. The governor was on a working visit on Thursday to assess the damages caused by Boko haram insurgents to the towns in the last 10 years. Speaking amidst cheers from the crowd, at the local government council secretariat, the Governor pledged to reconstruct all the destroyed structure and improve the economy of people in the area. He revealed that his administration will work towards providing access roads, health care services, portable drinking water and other infrastructural development. “Already, we have declared state of emergency in education from primary to secondary levels, and we would ensure that all other sectors of the economy have remarkably improved”, he said. The caretaker Chairman of Gujba local government, Kyari Batarama, expressed happiness over the governors visit and promise to give the administration maximum support for a better state.“ Gujba local government, where the new governor came from was once under the control of Boko haram insurgents for almost two years before the gallant troops of the Nigerian Army reclaimed the area. However, the area had suffered  incessant attacks by the insurgents in recent times where lives and property have been lost. Gov. Buni declares state of emergency on education in Yobe Insurgents take over military camps in Southern Yobe Boko Haram sacks towns in Yobe Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin